# riel-cursor-cli-hydra-claude-impl-workflow

Use this skill only when the user explicitly asks to run the hydra claude
workflow, for example "hydra claude workflow" or
`cursor-cli-hydra-claude-design-and-implement-review-loop`.

For ordinary implementation work, use the default
`riel-cursor-cli-impl-workflow`. If the user asks for hydra but does not say
whether to use the Codex or Claude hydra variant, ask for that choice before
running a workflow.

This file is packaged under `skills/cursor`, so project-scope package checkout
projects it to `.cursor/rules/riel-cursor-cli-hydra-claude-impl-workflow.mdc`
for Cursor and Cursor CLI runs from that project. Cursor rules are not
projected for user-scope installs.

## Workflow

Use the packaged workflow bundle:

- Workflow id: `cursor-cli-hydra-claude-design-and-implement-review-loop`
- Package id: `cursor-cli-hydra-claude-design-and-implement-review-loop`

Preferred entry point from the repository root:

```bash
bun run packages/rielflow/src/bin.ts workflow package checkout cursor-cli-hydra-claude-design-and-implement-review-loop
bun run packages/rielflow/src/bin.ts workflow run cursor-cli-hydra-claude-design-and-implement-review-loop --output json
```

Equivalent direct command:

```bash
rielflow workflow package checkout cursor-cli-hydra-claude-design-and-implement-review-loop
rielflow workflow run cursor-cli-hydra-claude-design-and-implement-review-loop --output json
```

## Model Routing

- Design and review agent steps: `claude-code-agent` with `claude-fable-5`
- Implementation step: `cursor-cli-agent` with `composer-2.5`
- Other agent steps: `claude-code-agent` with `claude-opus-4-8`

The implementation step includes its self-review prompt variant because that
variant belongs to the same workflow node.

## Runtime Inputs

Run the workflow in issue-resolution mode for normal implementation work.

Pass structured workflow input through `--variables` when the task needs
explicit issue/reference context. Typical fields:

- `workflowInput.issueUrl`
- `workflowInput.issueNumber`
- `workflowInput.issueRepository`
- `workflowInput.issueTitle`
- `workflowInput.issueBody`
- `workflowInput.targetFeatureArea`
- `workflowInput.requestedBehavior`
- `workflowInput.claudeCodeAgentReferences`
- `workflowInput.referenceRepositoryRoot`
- `workflowInput.referenceRepositoryUrl`

Planning-only mode is available via:

- `workflowInput.executionMode: "design-plan-only"`

## Reporting

After the workflow finishes, report workflow mode, changed files, verification
commands, commit message, commit hash, and pushed remote/branch.
